    <h4>Tabs vs Spaces: an epic battle</h4>
    <p>The "good" example above was made using spaces as tabs (when you git "tab" is produces spaces). If you look at the bottom-right of your sublime, you can choose how many spaces (or tabs) your editor should indent when you hit "tab":</p>

    <img style="width: 40%;" src="http://www.elevationacademy.co/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Screen-Shot-2016-03-14-at-6.18.49-AM.png">

    <p>Believe it or not, whether to indent with tabs or space is an epic <a href="https://www.jwz.org/doc/tabs-vs-spaces.html" target="_blank">nerd war</a> that we'd rather stay out of. For the sake of brevity, in our course we will use 2 spaces with every indentation.</p>
