  <div class="topic">
    <h4>Sublime Settings</h4>
    <p>Sublime's settings are changed with code... JSON to be exact. With Sublime open, go to <c>Preferences</c> - <c>Settings - Default</c>. You will see a list of options available to you to change your settings. Don't change this page. Instead, head to <c>Preferences</c> <c>Settings - User</c>. Depending, yours may or may not be blank. Go ahead and add the following code to that page and save:</p>

    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8">{
  <span style="color:#65b042">"font_size"</span>: <span style="color:#3387cc">14</span>,
  <span style="color:#65b042">"save_on_focus_lost"</span>: <span style="color:#3387cc">true</span>,
  <span style="color:#65b042">"tab_size"</span>: <span style="color:#3387cc">2</span>,
  <span style="color:#65b042">"translate_tabs_to_spaces"</span>: <span style="color:#3387cc">true</span>
}
</pre>

    <p>This will default your code to 2 tabs and will convert those tabs to spaces. Additionally, anytime you move from your Sublime to something else, it will automatically save whatever you were working on. Cool beans!</p>
